radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is dilated to 10 mm in diameter, fluid filled with several fecaliths, and with hyperemia of the wall. Mild surrounding inflammatory stranding present, but no extraluminal air or drainable collection. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and distal ureters are all within normal limits.
